description._content: PHOTO NUMBER: VPL 5384 DESCRIPTION: Two views of Stanley Park bridge, Vancouver, BC. Top: Town side of the bridge with people crossing. Two Chinese men coming from the bridge. Bottom: Approach to the bridge; trestles visible. Many people entering the park. The Vancouver Rowing Club is partially visible in the background. See also 5384A. Date: 1905 Photographer/Studio: Timms, Philip SUBJECTS: Bridges, Chinese Canadians, Pedestrians, Coal Harbour More information on our historical photograph collection: www.vpl.ca/historicalphotos
